  The evidence is clear: for low-risk pregnancies, staying home during early labor and arriving at the hospital in active labor leads to fewer interventions without compromising safety. The 3-1-1 rule --- contractions 3 minutes apart, lasting 1 minute, for 1 hour --- is a better threshold than the traditional 5-1-1, because it catches you closer to true active labor rather than the tail end of the latent phase.

